3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bitget calculates SEI/USDT funding rates using the premium/discount between perpetual and spot prices, combined with an interest rate component. The exchange applies funding every 8 hours with rates typically ranging from -0.1% to +0.1% per settlement. Position holders pay or receive funding based on their side - longs pay when rates are positive, shorts pay when negative. Bitget's maker fees of 0.02% and taker fees of 0.06% must be factored into arbitrage profitability calculations."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","SEI","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"SEI's position as a purpose-built trading-focused L1 blockchain creates unique funding dynamics driven by DeFi protocol launches and validator economics. The token's moderate liquidity on Bitget allows for meaningful arbitrage opportunities without excessive slippage. SEI's correlation with broader L1 narratives and periodic ecosystem announcements can create sustained funding rate imbalances suitable for multi-cycle arbitrage strategies."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"SEI/USDT funding rates on Bitget have shown pronounced cyclical behavior aligned with validator reward distributions and ecosystem milestones. During Q3-Q4 2024, rates averaged +0.02% per 8-hour cycle, with spikes to +0.08% during major DeFi protocol launches. Negative funding periods typically coincide with broader market downturns, creating opportunities for long-side arbitrage. The pair exhibits lower volatility in funding rates compared to newer altcoins, making it suitable for conservative arbitrage strategies with predictable risk profiles."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities and Setup"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"SEI/USDT arbitrage on Bitget works best during periods of ecosystem catalyst announcement when perpetual premiums spike above 0.05%. Traders can establish delta-neutral positions by shorting perpetuals while longing spot SEI on exchanges like Binance or OKX. Bitget's copy trading feature allows following successful SEI arbitrage strategies, though manual execution provides better control over entry timing. The 8-hour funding schedule enables three daily settlement opportunities, with typically higher rates during Asian trading hours when SEI ecosystem activity peaks."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"SEI arbitrage risks include basis risk from spot-perpetual price divergence and liquidity constraints during high volatility periods. Bitget's relatively newer market presence means lower SEI perpetual volumes compared to tier-1 exchanges, potentially causing wider spreads during stress periods. Position sizing should account for SEI's correlation with Cosmos ecosystem tokens and potential validator slashing events that could impact token economics. Funding rate reversals can occur rapidly during ecosystem developments, requiring tight stop-losses and position monitoring across the 8-hour cycles."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"What are typical SEI/USDT funding rates on Bitget?","answer":"SEI/USDT funding rates on Bitget typically range from -0.05% to +0.08% per 8-hour period, with an average positive bias due to long demand from SEI ecosystem participants. Rates above +0.05% generally indicate strong arbitrage opportunities."},{"question":"How does Bitget's fee structure affect SEI arbitrage profitability?","answer":"Bitget's 0.02% maker and 0.06% taker fees require minimum funding rates of approximately 0.04% per cycle to break even on roundtrip trades. VIP tier reductions can improve profitability thresholds for high-volume arbitrageurs."},{"question":"What makes SEI unique for funding rate arbitrage?","answer":"SEI's focus on trading infrastructure creates natural long bias in perpetuals from ecosystem participants, leading to more consistent positive funding rates. The token's moderate volatility also provides stable arbitrage conditions compared to higher-beta L1 alternatives."},{"question":"When do SEI funding rates typically spike on Bitget?","answer":"SEI funding rates often spike during DeFi protocol launches, validator reward distributions, and broader L1 narrative periods. Asian trading hours (08:00-16:00 UTC) frequently show higher rates due to increased ecosystem activity and retail participation."}]}]
